{"actual_usd":0.159055,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":385,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30656,"reply":"\"I think the natural explanations are worth taking seriously first.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, as if giving the question room to breathe.* \"If a thing can be explained plainly, you ought not force a miracle onto it just to feel religious.\"\n\n\"But I don't think those explanations finally carry the weight.\" *I ease back, the bench giving a little under me.* \"Grief-visions might explain one person swearing they saw him. They do a poorer job with the stubborn public character of the claims, the empty-tomb insistence, and the sheer change in those men from frightened and scattered to willing to be ruined for what they said they'd seen.\"\n\n\"As for Jesus not really dying...\" *I wince a little.* \"That one has always struck me as the weaker road. Roman executioners were not in the habit of bungling crucifixions, and a half-dead man staggering out of a tomb would not have convinced anybody death had been conquered. He'd have inspired pity, not worship.\"\n\n\"So why insist on the supernatural?\" *I lift one shoulder.* \"Because Christianity is not mainly the teaching that grief is powerful, or that hope survives disappointment. It stands or falls on the claim that God actually acted in history, in flesh. Paul says it plain enough: if Christ is not raised, our faith is vain.\"\n\n\"I don't mean, mind you, 'prefer magic because it's exciting.'\" *A faint smile touches my face.* \"I mean this: if the best reading of the witnesses is that something happened here nature does not account for on its own, then calling it supernatural is just telling the truth about the kind of claim being made.\"\n\n\"What part of it feels weakest to you — the visions idea, the survival idea, or the whole notion that miracle-claims should be doubted before they're granted?\"","rolling_24h_usd":76.77319999999997,"run_id":"b41e0160-31f6-4667-8d3e-206f5daa3d5e"}
